juniDhcpMIB.name: juniDhcpMIB

revisions.description: Added DHCP Option 60 support, and following objects become obsoleted: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerTable, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestIn, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseIn, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestOut, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseOut, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestDropped, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseDropped, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestBad, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseBad, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestDeleted, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsIn, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsOut, juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsDropped. Added juniDhcpRelayBroadcastFlagReplies to control unicast/broadcast delivery of DHCP reply packets. Added juniDhcpRelayGiaddrSelectsInterface for enable/diable of DHCP Relay Giaddr Selects Interface operation mode. Added juniDhcpRelayAgentVendorSpecificSuboption to configure the Vendor-Specific sub-option of the Relay Agent Info option.
Added new DHCP Relay statistics to juniDhcpRelayScalars.

Changed juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceName to be DisplayString type. Made index non-accessible. Added juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceTable to support per interface address limits. Added notification objects for pool groups.

Added juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsLeaseInterval, juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsLeaseStartTime and juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInitialLeaseStartTime. Update definition of juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsExpireTime. Added juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsRowStatus to permit administrative clearing of an address binding. Added juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSharedInUse to indicate sharing of DHCP pool addresses. Added statistics for renews, rebinds, errors, and discards. Added juniDhcpRelayLayer2UnicastReplies to control L2 ucast L3 bcast of DHCP reply packets.
Added ability to administratively delete DHCP local server address bindings.
Added new attributes juniDhcpLocalServerSnmpTrap and juniDhcpLocalServerInhibitRoaming. Also added juniDhcpLocalServerDuplicateClient notification.
Added DHCP local server pool exhaustion variables and notifications for high pool utilization and pool exhaustion.
Added support to exclude the subinterafce ID from option 82 circuit ID.
Added hostname and vrname scalars to DHCP Relay object. Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Added local server reservation and cable modem support. Refined agent info enable into agent circuit ID enable and agent remote ID enable.
Added support for DHCP Proxy Client under juniDhcpProxyClient node. Added additional error/discard statistics for DHCP Relay.
Initial version of this MIB module.

JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolName.name: JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolName
JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolName.description: DHCP Local Server Pool name. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set.
JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupName.name: JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupName
JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupName.description: DHCP Local Server Pool group name. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set. The pool group name is created by appending -Group to the name of the first pool in the group.
JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolDomainName.name: JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolDomainName
JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolDomainName.description: DHCP Local Server Pool domain name. Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set.
JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolDomainName.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetBiosNodeType.name: JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetBiosNodeType
JuniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetBiosNodeType.description: The set of netbios node types that may be assigned to the DHCP local server pool.

JuniDhcpLocalServerModeType.name: JuniDhcpLocalServerModeType
JuniDhcpLocalServerModeType.description: The set of DHCP Local Server operational Mode types.

JuniDhcpLocalServerPhysAddressString.name: JuniDhcpLocalServerPhysAddressString
JuniDhcpLocalServerPhysAddressString.description: DHCP local server MAC address. Represents the physical address in textual form, eg. 00-d0-b7-09-e0-00-00-00-00-00-00-00-00-00-00-00. Only hexidecimal digits (0-9, a-f) and the dash (-) from the NVT ASCII character set are valid.
JuniDhcpLocalServerPhysAddressString.reference: RFC 854: NVT ASCII character set. See SNMPv2-TC.DisplayString DESCRIPTION for a summary.

juniDhcpRelayAgentInfoEnable.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentInfoEnable
juniDhcpRelayAgentInfoEnable.description: Enable/disable use of the DHCP relay agent information option.

juniDhcpRelayBadMessages.name: juniDhcpRelayBadMessages
juniDhcpRelayBadMessages.description: Number of received DHCP relay messages that were discarded because their message operation (e.g. BOOTREQUEST, BOOTREPLY) was unknown, possibly due to corruption.

juniDhcpRelayUnknownMessages.name: juniDhcpRelayUnknownMessages

juniDhcpRelayAgentInfoAlreadyPresents.description: Number of received DHCP relay requests that were discarded because they already contained the Relay Agent Info option when this agent was configured to insert it.

juniDhcpRelayAgentCircuitIdEnable.description: Enable/disable use of the DHCP Relay Agent Info option Circuit Id suboption.

juniDhcpRelayAgentRemoteIdEnable.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentRemoteIdEnable
juniDhcpRelayAgentRemoteIdEnable.description: Enable/disable use of the DHCP Relay Agent Info option Remote Id suboption.

juniDhcpRelayAgentHostnameEnable.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentHostnameEnable
juniDhcpRelayAgentHostnameEnable.description: Enable/disable addition of Host Name to the DHCP Relay Agent Info option Circuit Id suboption.

juniDhcpRelayAgentVrnameEnable.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentVrnameEnable
juniDhcpRelayAgentVrnameEnable.description: Enable/disable addition of Virtual Router Name to the DHCP Relay Agent Info option Circuit Id suboption.

juniDhcpRelayAgentExcludeSubIdEnable.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentExcludeSubIdEnable
juniDhcpRelayAgentExcludeSubIdEnable.description: Enable/disable excluding of the subinterface identifier in the DHCP Relay Agent Info option Circuit Id suboption.

juniDhcpRelayAgentTrustAllEnable.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentTrustAllEnable
juniDhcpRelayAgentTrustAllEnable.description: Enable/disable Trust-all processing of the DHCP Relay Agent Info option.

juniDhcpRelayAgentInfoAlreadyPresentForw.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentInfoAlreadyPresentForwards
juniDhcpRelayAgentInfoAlreadyPresentForw.description: Number of received DHCP relay requests forwarded to DHCP server(s) that already contain the Relay Agent Info option.

juniDhcpRelayAgentGiaddrOverrides.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentGiaddrOverrides
juniDhcpRelayAgentGiaddrOverrides.description: Number of received DHCP relay requests whose giaddr field was overridden with IP address 0.0.0.0.

juniDhcpRelayAgentOptionOverrides.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentOptionOverrides
juniDhcpRelayAgentOptionOverrides.description: Number of received DHCP relay requests whose Relay Agent Info option was overridden with one created by this agent.

juniDhcpRelayDiscoverDiscards.name: juniDhcpRelayDiscoverDiscards
juniDhcpRelayDiscoverDiscards.description: Number of received DHCP relay Discover messages that were discarded because of lack of resources in this agent.

juniDhcpRelayPacketDiscards.name: juniDhcpRelayPacketDiscards
juniDhcpRelayPacketDiscards.description: Number of received DHCP relay messages, other than Discover messages, that were discarded because of lack of resource in this agent.

juniDhcpRelayUnknownRequestMessages.name: juniDhcpRelayUnknownRequestMessages
juniDhcpRelayUnknownRequestMessages.description: Number of received DHCP relay request messages that were discarded because their message type (e.g. Discover, Offer, Ack) was unknown, possibly due to corruption.

juniDhcpRelayUnknownReplyMessages.name: juniDhcpRelayUnknownReplyMessages
juniDhcpRelayUnknownReplyMessages.description: Number of received DHCP relay reply messages that were discarded because their message type (e.g. Discover, Offer, Ack) was unknown, possibly due to corruption.

juniDhcpRelayDuplicateRequestDiscards.name: juniDhcpRelayDuplicateRequestDiscards
juniDhcpRelayDuplicateRequestDiscards.description: Number of received DHCP relay requests that were discarded because they had a matching server address and XID of an outstanding DHCP server request.

juniDhcpRelayPacketsTransmitted.name: juniDhcpRelayPacketsTransmitted
juniDhcpRelayPacketsTransmitted.description: Number of DHCP relay requests successfully transmitted to DHCP servers.

juniDhcpRelayPacketsReceived.name: juniDhcpRelayPacketsReceived
juniDhcpRelayPacketsReceived.description: Number of DHCP relay replies successfully received from DHCP servers.

juniDhcpRelayUnknownXidDiscards.name: juniDhcpRelayUnknownXidDiscards
juniDhcpRelayUnknownXidDiscards.description: Number of DHCP relay replies received from DHCP servers that were discarded because their server address and XID did not match an outstanding DHCP server request.

juniDhcpRelayDroppedStaleRequestDiscards.name: juniDhcpRelayDroppedStaleRequestDiscards
juniDhcpRelayDroppedStaleRequestDiscards.description: Number of DHCP relay requests sent to DHCP server that were discarded because their replies timed out.

juniDhcpRelayLayer2UnicastReplies.name: juniDhcpRelayLayer2UnicastReplies
juniDhcpRelayLayer2UnicastReplies.description: Enable/disable the layer 2 unicast / layer 3 broadcast of DHCP reply packets to DHCP clients. Mutually exclusive with broadcast flag replies setting.

juniDhcpRelayGiaddrSelectsInterface.name: juniDhcpRelayGiaddrSelectsInterface
juniDhcpRelayGiaddrSelectsInterface.description: Enable/disable the determination of the client interface by the giaddr in the ACK message.

juniDhcpRelayAgentVendorSpecificSuboptio.name: juniDhcpRelayAgentVendorSpecificSuboption
juniDhcpRelayAgentVendorSpecificSuboptio.description: Enable/disable addition of the Layer 2 Circuit ID and/or User Packet Class to the Vendor-Specific sub-option of the DHCP Relay Agent Info option.

juniDhcpRelayBroadcastFlagReplies.name: juniDhcpRelayBroadcastFlagReplies
juniDhcpRelayBroadcastFlagReplies.description: Enable/disable using broadcast flag from the packet when sending DHCP reply packets to DHCP clients. Mutually exclusive with layer2 unicast replies setting.

juniDhcpRelayServerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a DHCP Relay server.

juniDhcpRelayServerAddress.name: juniDhcpRelayServerAddress

juniDhcpProxyClientUnknownServers.name: juniDhcpProxyClientUnknownServers

juniDhcpProxyClientServerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the DHCP Proxy servers known to the client.

juniDhcpProxyClientServerEntry.name: juniDhcpProxyClientServerEntry
juniDhcpProxyClientServerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a DHCP Proxy server known to the client.

juniDhcpProxyClientServerAddress.name: juniDhcpProxyClientServerAddress

juniDhcpProxyClientServerAdminStatus.name: juniDhcpProxyClientServerAdminStatus
juniDhcpProxyClientServerAdminStatus.description: Permits configuration of the client's operation status with respect to this server: disable Bar the client from using this server to obtain new address leases; and cause any leases from that server, that are currently in use by the client, to be released. drain Bar the client from using this server to obtain new address leases; but permit any leases from that server, that are currently in use by the client, to remain in use until they expire naturally. enabled Allow the client to use the server to obtain new address leases. Implementations that don't support administrative control of the server always report the value of enable(2), and disallow setting this object to any other value.

juniDhcpProxyClientServerOperStatus.name: juniDhcpProxyClientServerOperStatus
juniDhcpProxyClientServerOperStatus.description: Reports the client's current operation status with respect to this server: disabled The client is barred from using this server to obtain new address leases; and any leases from that server, that were in use by the client, have been released. draining The client is barred from using this server to obtain new address leases, but one or more leases from that server, that are in use by the client, will remain in use until they expire naturally. enabled The client may use the server to obtain new address leases, and may have one or more leases currently in use. Implementations that don't support administrative control of the server always report the value enabled(2).

juniDhcpProxyClientServerLeases.name: juniDhcpProxyClientServerLeases
juniDhcpProxyClientServerLeases.description: Total number of address leases granted to the client by this server (including those that have expired). The number of active leases from this server is determined by subtracting the value of juniDhcpProxyClientServerReleases from the value of this object.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsTable.description: A table of address bindings maintained by this DHCP Local Server.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsEntry.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsEntry
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an address binding maintained by this DHCP Local Server.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsIpAddress.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsIpAddress
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsIpAddress.description: The IP Address associated with this entry in the bindings table.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsPhysAddress.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsPhysAddress
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsPhysAddress.description: The Physical (MAC) Address associated with this entry in the bindings table and corresponding to the IP Address denoted by the table index.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInfinite.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInfinite
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInfinite.description: If true, then this binding will be maintained indefinitely. If false, then this binding will expire in accordance with the value of juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsExpireTime.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsExpireTime.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsExpireTime
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsExpireTime.description: If juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInfinite is false, then this is the time remaining prior to expiration of the address binding associated with this entry.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsRowStatus.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsRowStatus
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsRowStatus.description: Entries in this table are created only via DHCP operation, never via SNMP. Has the value active(1) when an entry exists. Set to destroy(6) to cause this IP address binding and user-specific routes to be removed. The effect is the same as if the user had released his address binding, or his address lease had expired. No other RowStatus enumeration values are supported.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsLeaseInterval.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsLeaseInterval
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsLeaseInterval.description: If juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInfinite is false, then this object is the time, in seconds, of the current lease.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsLeaseStartTim.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsLeaseStartTime
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsLeaseStartTim.description: The time the current lease was started.

juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInitialLeaseS.name: juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInitialLeaseStartTime
juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsInitialLeaseS.description: The initial time the lease was offered.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable.description: A table of address pools associated this DHCP Local Server. A DHCP Local Server may have multiple uniquely-named pools configured; however, only a single pool (with the name 'default') may have a network address and mask assigned.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolEntry.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolEntry
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an address pool associated this DHCP Local Server.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolName.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolName
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolName.description: The name of the local server pool to which this entry belongs. Only an entry with the name 'default' may have a network address and mask assigned.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolDomainName.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolDomainName
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolDomainName.description: The domain name assigned to this local server pool. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null string) and then modified (via set to new string).

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetworkIpAddress.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetworkIpAddress
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetworkIpAddress.description: The IP Address assigned to this local server pool. This object must be set in conjunction with juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetworkMask. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null IP address) and then modified (via set to new IP address). Only configurable/valid for entries with the index name (juniDhcpLocalServerPoolName) 'default'.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetworkMask.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetworkMask
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetworkMask.description: The network mask assigned to this local server pool. This object must be set in conjunction with juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetworkIpAddress. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null IP mask) and then modified (via set to new IP mask). Only configurable/valid for entries with the index name (juniDhcpLocalServerPoolName) 'default'.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetBiosNodeType.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetBiosNodeType
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNetBiosNodeType.description: The NetBios node type assigned to this local server pool.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolLeaseTime.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolLeaseTime
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolLeaseTime.description: The time interval for address renewal required of a client using the address associated with this local server pool entry. Setting a zero value will effect an infinite lease, which in turn is indicated by the value -1 returned via a get.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryDnsServer.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryDnsServer
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryDnsServer.description: The address of the primary DNS Server associated with this local server pool. This object must be set in conjunction with juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryDnsServer. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null IP address) and then modified (via set to new IP address).

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryDnsServe.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryDnsServer
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryDnsServe.description: The address of the secondary DNS Server associated with this local server pool. This object must be set in conjunction with juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryDnsServer. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null IP address) and then modified (via set to new IP address).

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryNetBiosNam.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryNetBiosNameServer
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryNetBiosNam.description: The address of the primary NetBios Name Server associated with this local server pool. This object must be set in conjunction with juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryNetBiosNameServer. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null IP address) and then modified (via set to new IP address).

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryNetBiosN.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryNetBiosNameServer
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryNetBiosN.description: The address of the secondary NetBios Name Server associated with this local server pool. This object must be set in conjunction with juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryNetBiosNameServer. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null IP address) and then modified (via set to new IP address).

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryDefaultRou.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryDefaultRouter
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryDefaultRou.description: The address of the primary Default Router associated with this local server pool. This object must be set in conjunction with juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryDefaultRouter. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null IP address) and then modified (via set to new IP address).

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryDefaultR.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryDefaultRouter
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSecondaryDefaultR.description: The address of the secondary Default Router associated with this local server pool. This object must be set in conjunction with juniDhcpLocalServerPoolPrimaryDefaultRouter. Modification of extant values for this object require that it first be cleared (via set to null IP address) and then modified (via set to new IP address).

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolLinkName.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolLinkName
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolLinkName.description: The name of this local server pool's backup pool.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolHighUtilThreshold.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolHighUtilThreshold
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolHighUtilThreshold.description: The value of address pool utilization, where if reached for the first time, will generate a high address pool utilization event to the management entity on this system. The value of this object must be greater than the value of juniDhcpLocalServerPoolAbatedUtilThreshold. The following pseudo-code states when high address pool utilization notification will be generated comparing this object value to the value of juniDhcpLocalServerPoolUtilPct object. Address pool utilization state will be set to 'ok' when the pool was created first time and after that it will only be set in the context of and while triggering high and abated threshold notifications. if ( percentageOfAddressPoolUtil >= percentageOfAddressPoolHighUtilThreshold ) { if ( addressPoolUtilState == addressPoolUtilStateOk ) { addressPoolUtilState = addressPoolUtilStateWarning; if ( addressPoolUtilTrapsEnabled ) triggerAddressPoolHighUtilTrap(); } }

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolAbatedUtilThresho.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolAbatedUtilThreshold
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolAbatedUtilThresho.description: The value of address pool utilization that is used to determine when to generate an abated address pool utilization event notification to the management entity on this system. The value of this object must be less than the value of the juniDhcpLocalServerPoolHighUtilThreshold. The abated address pool utilization event is sent once if the high address pool utilization threshold is reached and utilization falls to the value of this object. The following pseudo-code states when abated address pool utilization notification will be generated comparing this object value to the value of juniDhcpLocalServerPoolUtilPct object. Address pool utilization state will be set to 'ok' when the pool was created first time and after that it will only be set in the context of and while triggering high and abated threshold notifications. if ( percentageOfAddressPoolUtil >= percentageOfAddressPoolAbatedUtilThreshold ) { if ( addressPoolUtilState == addressPoolUtilStateWarning ) { addressPoolUtilState = addressPoolUtilStateOk; if ( addressPoolUtilTrapsEnabled ) triggerAddressPoolAbatedUtilTrap(); } }

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolUtilPct.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolUtilPct
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolUtilPct.description: The current address utilization for this pool. When all the addresses in the pool are exhausted this object value becomes 100, i.e, poolUtil = 100%. When the pool reaches this stage, there won't be anymore addresses available from the pool. Any attempt to allocate an address from the pool will each time result in a juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNoAddresses notification.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapEnable.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapEnable
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapEnable.description: The configuration setting for address pool notifications. Setting this object to true(1) will enable the sending of address pool event notifications to the management entity on this device. Setting this object to false(2) will disable event notification reports.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolInUse.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolInUse
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolInUse.description: The number of addresses currently allocated from this pool.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSize.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSize
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSize.description: The number of addresses available in this pool.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSharedInUse.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSharedInUse
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolSharedInUse.description: The number of addresses currently allocated from this pool to an application other than DHCP.

juniDhcpLocalServerAttributesMode.name: juniDhcpLocalServerAttributesMode
juniDhcpLocalServerAttributesMode.description: An object representing the mode in which the DHCP Local Server is operating.

juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceTable.name: juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceTable
juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceTable.description: A table of subinterface configuration maintained by this DHCP Local Server.

juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceEntry.name: juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceEntry
juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a subinterface binding for this DHCP Local Server. Rows in this table cannot be created via SNMP. They are created at run time by the Local Server

juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceIndex.name: juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceIndex
juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceIndex.description: The index value of this table entry.

juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceName.name: juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceName
juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceName.description: The string that identifies the subinterface for this entry.

juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceLimit.name: juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceLimit
juniDhcpLocalServerSubInterfaceLimit.description: The number of clients allowed by the local server on this subinterface.

juniDhcpLocalServerSnmpTrap.name: juniDhcpLocalServerSnmpTrap
juniDhcpLocalServerSnmpTrap.description: An object that determines whether or not the DHCP Local Server generates SNMP traps when conditions that trigger traps occur.

juniDhcpLocalServerInhibitRoaming.name: juniDhcpLocalServerInhibitRoaming
juniDhcpLocalServerInhibitRoaming.description: An object representing the mode in which the DHCP Local Server is operating as it pertains to roaming clients.

juniDhcpLocalServerUniqueClientIds.name: juniDhcpLocalServerUniqueClientIds
juniDhcpLocalServerUniqueClientIds.description: An object representing the mode in which the DHCP Local Server is operating as it pertains to allowing multiple clients having identical client IDs or hardware addresses.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupTable.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupTable
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupTable.description: A table of address pool groups associated this DHCP Local Server. A DHCP Local Server may have multiple uniquely-named pool groups configured. This table is only used for pool group traps.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupEntry.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupEntry
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an address pool group associated this DHCP Local Server.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupName.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupName
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupName.description: The name of the local server pool group to which this entry belongs.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupSize.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupSize
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupSize.description: Total number of addresses in the pool group for utilization events.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupInUse.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupInUse
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupInUse.description: Total number of addresses in use for pool group for utilization events.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupUtilPct.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupUtilPct
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupUtilPct.description: Percentage of pool addresses in use for pool group for utilization events.

juniDhcpLocalServerReservesTable.name: juniDhcpLocalServerReservesTable
juniDhcpLocalServerReservesTable.description: A table of pool name, MAC address, and IP address reservation groups that are maintained by this DHCP Local Server.

juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntry.name: juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntry
juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an MAC address, IP address, pool name reservation maintained by this DHCP Local Server.

juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryIpAddres.name: juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryIpAddress
juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryIpAddres.description: The IP Address associated with this entry in reserves table.

juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryPoolName.name: juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryPoolName
juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryPoolName.description: The name of the local server pool associated with this entry in the reserves table and corresponding to the IP Address denoted by the table index.

juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryPhysAddr.name: juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryPhysAddress
juniDhcpLocalServerReservesEntryPhysAddr.description: The physical (MAC) address string associated with this entry in the reserves table and corresponding to the IP Address denoted by the table index.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerTable.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerTable
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the DHCP Cable Modem Relay servers.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerEntry.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerEntry
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a DHCP Cable Modem DHCP server.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerEntry.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerEntryAddress
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemServerEntry.description: The IP address of the DHCP server to which DHCP requests received from attached Cable Modem DHCP clients are forwarded.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestIn.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestIn
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestIn.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Client Requests that are received.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseIn.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseIn
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseIn.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Server Responses that are received.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestOut.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestOut
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestOut.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Client Request that are transmitted.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseOut.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseOut
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseOut.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Server Responses that are transmitted.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestDrop.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestDropped
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestDrop.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Client Request that are dropped.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseDro.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseDropped
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseDro.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Server Responses that are dropped.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestBad.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestBad
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestBad.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Client Request that are bad.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseBad.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseBad
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemResponseBad.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Server Responses that are bad.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestDele.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestDeleted
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemRequestDele.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Requests that were deleted because they were stale.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsIn.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsIn
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsIn.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Packets received.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsOut.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsOut
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsOut.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Packets transmitted.

juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsDrop.name: juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsDropped
juniDhcpLocalServerCableModemPacketsDrop.description: The number of Cable Modem DHCP Packets dropped.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolHighAddrUtil.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolHighAddrUtil
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolHighAddrUtil.description: Reports when the address pool utilization has reached the configured high utilization threshold. See the DESCRIPTIONs for the juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable elements for details on what conditions trigger a high pool utilization notification.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolAbatedAddrUtil.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolAbatedAddrUtil
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolAbatedAddrUtil.description: Reports when the address pool utilization has fallen to the configured abated threshold level. See the DESCRIPTIONs for the juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable elements for details on what conditions trigger a abated pool utilization notification.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNoAddresses.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNoAddresses
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolNoAddresses.description: Reports when the address pool has exhausted its supply of addresses. This trap is issued every time a request is made to allocate an address from a fully utilized pool. See the DESCRIPTIONs for the juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable elements for details on what conditions trigger a no address pool utilization notification.

juniDhcpLocalServerHealth.name: juniDhcpLocalServerHealth
juniDhcpLocalServerHealth.description: Reports when a health event occurs in the DhcpLocalServer application on the router identified by juniRouterName.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupHighAddrUtil.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupHighAddrUtil
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupHighAddrUtil.description: Reports when the address pool group utilization has reached the configured high utilization threshold. See the DESCRIPTIONs for the juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable elements for details on what conditions trigger a high pool group utilization notification.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupAbatedAddrUt.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupAbatedAddrUtil
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupAbatedAddrUt.description: Reports when the address pool group utilization has fallen to the configured abated threshold level. See the DESCRIPTIONs for the juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable elements for details on what conditions trigger a abated pool group utilization notification.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupNoAddresses.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupNoAddresses
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolGroupNoAddresses.description: Reports when the address pool group has exhausted its supply of addresses. This trap is issued every time a request is made to allocate an address from a fully utilized pool. See the DESCRIPTIONs for the juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTable elements for details on what conditions trigger a no address pool group utilization notification.

juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceLimitExceede.name: juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceLimitExceeded
juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceLimitExceede.description: Reports when a subinterface has exceeded the limit of clients allowed on that subinterface.

juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceLimitAbated.name: juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceLimitAbated
juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceLimitAbated.description: Reports when the number of clients on a subinterface has fallen below the limit allowed on that subinterface.

juniDhcpLocalServerDuplicateClient.name: juniDhcpLocalServerDuplicateClient
juniDhcpLocalServerDuplicateClient.description: Reports the first occurance of detection of a DHCP client that changed interfaces.

juniDhcpLocalServerEventSeverity.name: juniDhcpLocalServerEventSeverity
juniDhcpLocalServerEventSeverity.description: The syslog severity of this server health event

juniDhcpLocalServerEventString.name: juniDhcpLocalServerEventString
juniDhcpLocalServerEventString.description: The text of the event string associated with the server health event

juniDhcpLocalServerMacAddress.name: juniDhcpLocalServerMacAddress
juniDhcpLocalServerMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the client that changed interfaces.

juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceString.name: juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceString
juniDhcpLocalServerInterfaceString.description: The interface where the DHCP client was detected

juniDhcpLocalServerLastDetected.name: juniDhcpLocalServerLastDetected
juniDhcpLocalServerLastDetected.description: The time the duplicate client was last detected

juniDhcpRelayCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP Relay. This statement became obsolete when Local Server support objects were added.

juniDhcpProxyCompliance.name: juniDhcpProxyCompliance
juniDhcpProxyCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP Proxy. This statement became obsolete when Local Server support objects were added.

juniDhcpCompliance.name: juniDhcpCompliance
juniDhcpCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP. This compliance statement became obsolete when support was added for reservations and cable modem servers.

juniDhcpCompliance2.name: juniDhcpCompliance2
juniDhcpCompliance2.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP. This compliance statement became obsolete when support was added for adding host name or virtual router name to relay agent option 82.

juniDhcpCompliance3.name: juniDhcpCompliance3
juniDhcpCompliance3.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP. This compliance statement became obsolete when support was added for excluding the subinterface ID from relay agent option 82.

juniDhcpCompliance4.name: juniDhcpCompliance4
juniDhcpCompliance4.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP. This compliance statement became obsolete when support was added for DHCP local address pool utilizations support.

juniDhcpCompliance5.name: juniDhcpCompliance5
juniDhcpCompliance5.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP. This compliance statement became obsolete when support was added for the DHCP Relay Trust-all mode.

juniDhcpCompliance6.name: juniDhcpCompliance6
juniDhcpCompliance6.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP. This compliance statement became obsolete when support was added to administratively delete entries in juniDhcpLocalServerBindingsTable.

juniDhcpCompliance7.name: juniDhcpCompliance7
juniDhcpCompliance7.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP.

juniDhcpCompliance8.name: juniDhcpCompliance8
juniDhcpCompliance8.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP. This compliance statement became obsolete when support was added for new DHCP Relay statistics in juniDhcpRelayScalars.

juniDhcpCompliance9.name: juniDhcpCompliance9
juniDhcpCompliance9.description: Obsolete compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP.

juniDhcpCompliance10.name: juniDhcpCompliance10
juniDhcpCompliance10.description: The compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP.

juniDhcpCompliance11.name: juniDhcpCompliance11
juniDhcpCompliance11.description: The compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP.

juniDhcpCompliance12.name: juniDhcpCompliance12
juniDhcpCompliance12.description: The compliance statement for systems supporting DHCP.

juniDhcpRelayGroup.name: juniDhcpRelayGroup
juniDhcpRelayGroup.description: Obsolete collection of basic objects providing management of DHCP Relay functionality. This group became obsolete when the agent info enable was divided into agent circuit ID enable and agent remote ID enable.

juniDhcpProxyGroup.name: juniDhcpProxyGroup
juniDhcpProxyGroup.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of DHCP Proxy functionality.

juniDhcpLocalServerGroup.name: juniDhcpLocalServerGroup
juniDhcpLocalServerGroup.description: Obsolete basic collection of objects providing management of DHCP Local Server functionality. This group became obsolete when support was added for reservations and cable modem servers.

juniDhcpLocalServerGroup2.name: juniDhcpLocalServerGroup2
juniDhcpLocalServerGroup2.description: Obsolete basic collection of objects providing management of DHCP Local Server functionality. This group became obsolete when support was added for DHCP local pool utilization.

juniDhcpRelayGroup2.name: juniDhcpRelayGroup2
juniDhcpRelayGroup2.description: Obsolete basic collection of objects providing management of DHCP Relay functionality. This group became obsolete when support was added for adding host name or virtual router name to Option 82 circuit ID field.

juniDhcpRelayGroup3.name: juniDhcpRelayGroup3
juniDhcpRelayGroup3.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of DHCP Relay functionality. This group became obsolete when support was added for excluding the subinterface ID in the Option 82 circuit ID field.

juniDhcpRelayGroup4.name: juniDhcpRelayGroup4
juniDhcpRelayGroup4.description: Obsolete collection of objects providing management of DHCP Relay functionality. This group became obsolete when support was added for the Trust-all mode.

juniDhcpRelayDeprecatedGroup.name: juniDhcpRelayDeprecatedGroup
juniDhcpRelayDeprecatedGroup.description: Deprecated object providing management of DHCP Relay functionality. This group became deprecated when the agent info enable was divided into agent circuit ID enable and agent remote ID enable.

juniDhcpLocalServerGroup3.name: juniDhcpLocalServerGroup3
juniDhcpLocalServerGroup3.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of DHCP Local Server functionality.

juniDhcpLocalServerGroup4.name: juniDhcpLocalServerGroup4
juniDhcpLocalServerGroup4.description: Deprecated DHCP Local Server group of objects providing management of DHCP Local Server functionality. This object became deprecated when the Duplicate Client trap was added

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapGroup.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapGroup
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapGroup.description: Deprecated notifications providing alarms for high pool utilization and pool exhaustion of DHCP local address pools. This was deprecated when the roaming client trap was added.

juniDhcpRelayGroup5.name: juniDhcpRelayGroup5
juniDhcpRelayGroup5.description: Obsolete basic collection of objects providing management of DHCP Relay functionality.

juniDhcpLocalServerGroup5.name: juniDhcpLocalServerGroup5
juniDhcpLocalServerGroup5.description: Obsolete basic collection of objects providing management of DHCP Local Server functionality.

juniDhcpLocalServerGroup6.name: juniDhcpLocalServerGroup6
juniDhcpLocalServerGroup6.description: Obsolete basic collection of objects providing management of DHCP Local Server functionality.

juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapGroup2.name: juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapGroup2
juniDhcpLocalServerPoolTrapGroup2.description: Obsolete notifications providing alarms for high pool utilization and pool exhaustion of DHCP local address pools and interface limit events.
